  "notes": "## Mahnwesen (Dunning) - FIXED v2\n\n### Audit Changes\n- FIXED: Table changed from 'invoices' to 'rechnungen' (correct Supabase schema table)\n- FIXED: Replaced $credentials.openAiApi.apiKey inline expression with $env[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"] env var\n- FIXED: Column references updated to rechnungen schema (brutto, mahnstufe, letzte_mahnung instead of total, dunning_level, dunning_sent_at)\n- FIXED: Removed references to non-existent 'jobs_queue' table; replaced with automation_log (exists in schema)\n- ADDED: Is Overdue? IF node to skip invoices still within payment terms\n- ADDED: Error Handler node to log failures to automation_log\n- ADDED: continueOnFail on GPT and PDF nodes to prevent silent failures\n\n### Setup Required\n1. **Credentials**: Set up 'Supabase API' credential in n8n (Settings > Credentials > New > Supabase API)\n2. **Env Vars**: Set OPENAI_API_KEY and PDF_GENERATION_WEBHOOK_URL in n8n environment\n3. **Schema**: rechnungen table must have: mahnstufe INTEGER DEFAULT 0, letzte_mahnung TIMESTAMPTZ (added via migration in supabase-schema.sql)\n4. **Activate**: Toggle workflow to Active in n8n\n\n### Dunning Levels\n- < 14 days: Zahlungserinnerung (gentle reminder) -> mahnstufe=1\n- 14-30 days: 1. Mahnung (first notice) -> mahnstufe=2\n- 30-60 days: 2. Mahnung (second notice) -> mahnstufe=3\n- > 60 days: Letzte Mahnung vor Inkasso (final notice before collections) -> mahnstufe=4"
}
